 was alot of good and bad on this raid. <br>
<br>
I was really amazed at the turn out. We had 7 groups going in. That says alot for what we as a guild can do. <br>
<br>
We had alot of people who did not know the zone, and had not read the guide to the zone. That compounded the problems of trying to move such a large group through the narrow tunnel that are so common here. I am very happy to say we did not have train problems on the raid and that was a major worry I had. Dealing with the mermaids we had a few deaths with the larger encounters but these were on the order of 4 or less each time they happened. Estrella and Shellara both went down with ease. <br>
<br>
One of the biggest problems I had was trying to keep track of everything. This was a problem because people were chatting in OOC alot. I had designated that channel for raid and group leaders, so I could filter alot of the other stuff out. it may not seem like a big deal to most but when stuff scrolls of before you can get reports from a group, its hard to track what the status of the various groups are. <br>
<br>
We only had one cleric which slowed us down alot for Rezes. And some of the groups did not have enough healing power, those were primarily groups 5 and up which were formed at the meeting site as pick up groups. <br>
<br>
Group 3, Veldar's group, did a great job as artillery. Thier timing was right on the money. No mob stayed up for very long once they opened up. <br>
<br>
Group 4, Amanar's group, handled the job of controling any added casting mobs well. Any time there were more than a couple Mermaids they were right on the additional add to keep it from healing the one we were fighting.<br>
<br>
All in all I am happy with the job everyone on that raid did. In my opinion this was a learning raid and as a guild we took away several lessons and some good experience. it is not easy to fight when you have to watch up and down in addition to around you. Add to that lots of narrow twisting passages and you have a tough place to fight. If we can learn to fight well in this kind of an enviroment there is no place we can't fight. <br>
<br>
We did have one death from drowning in the raid, which alone says alot about how well we did in there. I won't mention the persons name but they could cast EB. <br>
<br>
I would like to get a group or two together on a regular basis to hunt this zone. The XP in here is pretty good even into the low 50s. And that will give us our future group leaders for raids into this zone. I know our Mages, and Druids have parts of thier Epics in here, as well as Wizards, Rangers, and Paladins all having quests that involve this zone. <br>
<br>
In closing I would like to say I welcome any and all comments people may have that were on this raid. I think the feed back will be a help in the planning of future raids here.<br>
<br>
Benadan<br>
