<br>
I made the call to pull back and I will take the heat for it if you want to dish it out to someone. Here is what I was thinking at the time so you can better understand my reasoning. First, the raid party had devolved to an unruly mob, and had done so in a dangerous location. We were getting deaths because of that fact. I felt it better to pull everyone back to a safer location and restore order to the raid before proceeding deeper. Second, We had a fair number of people LD at various points during the raid. Each time I was aware of an LD we as a whole waited for that person to get back. A few times the raid group was chomping at the bit because of the wait. In those cases I was setting 2 groups to wait for and protect the LD, while the rest of us moved forward. By the time we got back to the second level of Kedge, it was obvious that order was not going to be restored so I called the raid at that point. Several people had Xloced or ported out already by that point. <br>
<br>
I purposely stayed in Kedge until the last of our people were out to make sure no one was left in that dungeon. Thiose people who did meet up at unrest, the designated meeting point after we left Kedge, did roll on the items. It was there that Denkar was given sufficent money to purchase a coffin so he could summon Assim's corpse, which we had not been able to find. Unfortunately Assim was not on line at that time and Sunday evening Denkar was not online while Assim was so we purchased a second coffin and Bam summoned the corpse. <br>
<br>
My personal feeling about leading a raid is very simple. I do not want any unnecessary deaths on the raid PERIOD. I know deaths will happen in a fight it is part of the game. But to go into an area that is hazardous with a group that forany reason is questionable about being able to handle those dangers is asking for unnecessary deaths.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/ukajirafirelite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KajiraFirelite</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://members.tripod.co.uk/redhotant/icons/iconoc01.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 459<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/5/01 12:05:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.sonic.net/~rodney1/wolfblue.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kedge -the aftermath</span><hr size=1> wise choice. . .totally supported it<br>
