opic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Kedge  - The aftermath</span><hr size=1> The shrink potions for everybody except raid leader and group leaders sounds like a wise tactic (perhaps expensive, though). That way, even if they don't lead by communication, you can at least see who to follow without having to resort to autofollow (which is useless in Kedge due to Z axis). Of course, if you have bad communication you're just going to go around in circles anyway... <br>
<br>
Group leaders - please relay instructions you receive from the raid leader to your groups. This will allow raid leaders to use /tells to give instructions and will cut down on blabber-scroll. Group leaders on normal xp runs are usually just a member of the group who happened to invite first -- raids are different. You need to LEAD! Please SAY you are moving from one location to another before you do it, and make sure all of your people are formed up and READY to move. In some places, where aggro is insane, this can be a life saver. People on a raid naturally want to help and, in a command vaccuum, may actually do harm by &quot;volunteering&quot;. If there are seven groups on a raid and the leader is targeting a mob that needs two groups to kill (s)he may send in three with a safety margin and hold four in reserve for pops and to prevent confusion. TELL your people you're in the reserves if you receive a group-order to hold back, and to report additional pops if they see any. Keeping track of group members and keeping them informed is critical to ensure good cross-class coordination.<br>
<br>
Perhaps having group leaders assigned in advance and briefed in a pre-raid leaders' only meeting might be useful?<br>
<br>
These are just my thoughts. I hope somebody finds them useful.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/ubenadan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Benadan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/6/01 8:11:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Kedge  - The aftermath</span><hr size=1> Some real good points there Bauldor. When I led Perm raids way back when I had the group leaders show up the night before and we went through the areas we were going to hit invis, basically a walk thru of the zone.<br>
<br>
As for shrink, a shaman in each group or even moving group to group can take care of that one. Hmm not sure if I can shrink gnomes dwarves or halfings though, they might diappear if they get any smaller. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
