I agree with all of the above posts...nothing to add but that we need to do this zone again and again and again! Not only are there nice items for all classes to be had, but those blond bishes are gem droppers waiting to be farmed! Not to mention that this is one zone unique to Norrath, and, with the right discipline, EH can Own people. I vote for Lather, Rinse, and Repeat. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/ubenadan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Benadan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/7/01 2:49:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=28.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: KK/CR</span><hr size=1> Assim, Helping with the CR was Mox nix. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I too got an invite to that little party we had in the desert back in 91. What a joy it was 135 in the shade and there ain't no F***ing shade!<br>
<br>
My personal thought is that every raid should get a thread like this one so we can examine what went right and wrong on the raid and refine our strategies for raiding. Our numbers alone can make us the best raiding force on the server. Add to that the ability of our members to function as a well oiled machine in any zone and no other guild could touch us.<br>
<br>
It seems a major issue here is communication during the raid. So to that end I propose this protocol for communications, in Kedge specifically, and possibly for other raids as well.<br>
1. Guild chat to be turned off at the start of the raid by all but the raid leaders. <br>
2. 2 channels be specified by the raid leadership, one as a command channel and the second as general chat. (such as ooc for command, and shout for chat)<br>
3. The use of tells be minimized. Even using r and tab to scroll through the names it can be very time consuming to have to reply to everyone individually.<br>
4. Voice any concerns to your group leader. They will pass them to the raid leader or ask you to send the raid leader a tell, based on the response they get from the raid leader. if you don't feel your concern was addressed properly during the raid, voice it here on the message board when things are more relaxed.<br>
5. if you are truely unhappy with the way a raid is going you can ask for a tranlocate.<br>
6. Raid leaders and group leaders do a pre-raid wal thru of the zone if possible. <br>
7. Utilize shrink as much as possible to aid in making leaders stand out a bit.<br>
8. Movement to be down in 1 or 2 group teams, instead of the entire raid moving at once. <br>
9. 2 group teams consist of a melle group and a caster group. <br>
10. Allow folks below the listed level to attend the raid if possible, but at thier own risk. <br>
<br>
I would like to explain point 10 in a bit of detail at this point. We had a lvl 30 shaman with us in Kedge, sorry I forget the exact name. She did an excellent job healing the Caster group! Allowing these folks to join us if they are willing to take the risk provides them with excellent experience in raiding, if not in terms of game xp as well. If they are getting game xp they are in effect getting PLed a bit by it. My one reservation on this point is Kedge specific though. I am very nervous about allowing any caster under 35 on these raids. The reason is medding, they cannot see thier buffs while medding and could easily have EB run out on them without warning.<br>
<br>
11. One or two groups, depending on the dangers in the area, be designated to guard LDs locations until thier return.<br>
12. Use of a social with the /assist (MA) is manditory.<br>
13. Kedge Specific, A social that contains all five lines saying Endure Breathing in /gsay. Five lines simply to prevent it from getting lost in battle scroll. <br>
14. Kedge Specific, Water stones. One or more Mages are essential to this zone for safety. Everyone should have 2 water stones on them at all times. After using your EB hotkey, if you still do not have EB cast upon you my the time you are down 2 bubbles on your breath bar, use a water stone. Then when the situation permits let your group leader know you are going to a mage to get a replacement. Drowning is totally unnecessary in this zone if we are smart.<br>
15. Corpses, will all be recovered if possible before the raid leadership leaves the raid site. This may involve a meeting outside the zone being raided and arrangements being made for coffins, then a re entry to the raid zone.<br>
16. In the event of some one logging before thier corpse has been recovered. A team will be designated to return with the person the next day to recover the corpse.<br>
<br>
I think this sums up what has been covered in this thread.<br>
